         <abstract>
            <p>A recent article in this journal by D. G. Korn and J. J. Lambiotte, Jr. discusses implementations of the FFT algorithm on the CDC STAR-100 vector computer. The `Pease'-algorithm is recommended in cases when only a few transforms can be performed simultaneously. We show how the use of a different algorithm and of trigonometric tables will lead to more than three times faster execution times. The times for large transforms increase only about 39% if the tables are eliminated in order to save storage.</p>
          </abstract>
